Class FibCounterTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • FibCounterTest

  • public class FibCounterTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Junit test class for FibCounter. It performs test cases for incrementing count, decrementing count, getting current count, and fetching fibonacci number for the current count.

      Initialises Fibonacci counter with default values.
      void testDecrementCountBaseCase()
      Calls decrementCount of FibCounter to test for the test case where counter is incremented and decremented by 1 successfully, i.e, base case for calculating Fibonacci number.
      void testDecrementCountMinCount()
      Calls decrementCount of FibCounter to test for the test case where counter cannot be decremented successfully.
      void testDecrementCountSuccess()

      Calls getFibonacci of FibCounter to test for the test case where fibonacci number is returned after incrementing and decrementing counter n times.
